id: monica-config-output-secret-sink
title: Prevent configuration secrets from reaching logging sinks
description: Eliminate the generic console logging sink used by config commands so masked configuration output remains safe by construction and GitHub code scanning has zero open alerts.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[5]: codeql,config,credentials,release-gate,security
created_at: "2026-07-21T22:47:37.960Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T22:58:02.114Z"
deadline: "2026-07-22T00:00:00.000Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T22:51:47.304Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: Config output uses a non-logging structured stdout sink; API keys and passwords remain masked in every config read/show/setup/set response; focused and full tests retain exact 100/100/100/100 coverage; CodeQL security workflow succeeds with zero open alerts on the new merged head; package is not published
definition_of_ready: "All-status PM search completed with no duplicate; exact alert, commit, path, and sink identified."
goal: Secure agent-ready Monica CLI
objective: Maintain zero high-severity code-scanning findings on the default branch
value: Prevents credential disclosure regressions in the local settings interface.
impact: Protects Monica API tokens and user credentials while preserving programmatic output.
why_now: The otherwise-green merged API parity release surfaced an exact-head high-severity CodeQL alert.
parent: monica-platform
reviewer: codex-root
risk: high
confidence: 100
sprint: 2026-07-21-security-closeout
release: 2026.7.21-2
reporter: GitHub CodeQL
severity: high
environment: GitHub Security workflow on merged master 809fe40794bb9f1ce8f18181fcb78fc39115d438
repro_steps: Open GitHub code-scanning alert 10 or run the Security workflow against merged commit 809fe407; inspect src/commands/config.ts line 29.
resolution: Replaced the generic console.log configuration sink with process.stdout.write of the already-formatted structured payload and added focused regression coverage proving masked config reads do not invoke console.log.
expected_result: Configuration commands emit validated structured output without any secret-capable console logging sink; all tests and security scans pass; open CodeQL alerts return to zero.
actual_result: PR #60 exact head 54cd3304e1cf27d14eeda5c586bd86beb402ec82 completed both CodeQL checks successfully and the PR-scoped open code-scanning alert inventory returned zero.
affected_version: 2026.7.21-2
fixed_version: 2026.7.21-2
component: config-output
regression: false
