comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T22:47:37.960Z",codex-root,Duplicate-safe all-status search found no existing item for CodeQL alert 10. This is a focused post-merge security remediation linked to the API parity delivery and platform epic.
  "2026-07-21T22:48:44.618Z",codex-root,Implementation replaces the generic console.log config sink with structured stdout output and adds a regression assertion that masked config reads never invoke console.log. The release remains 2026.7.21-2 because that candidate is merged but intentionally untagged and unpublished.
  "2026-07-21T22:58:02.114Z",codex-root,"CodeRabbit correctly requested explicit gated proof. GitHub CodeQL completed successfully twice on PR #60 head 54cd3304e1cf27d14eeda5c586bd86beb402ec82, and GET /code-scanning/alerts?state=open&pr=60 returned an empty alert set. The close event is therefore backed by exact-head security evidence before merge; default-branch inventory will be repeated after merge."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T22:47:37.960Z",codex-root,"Do not place live credentials in PM metadata, source, tests, commits, PR text, or logs. Verification must use synthetic tokens and GitHub alert metadata only."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T22:47:37.960Z",codex-root,A passing CodeQL workflow means analysis completed successfully; it does not imply the repository has zero open findings. Exact-head alert inventory is a separate mandatory release proof.
  "2026-07-21T22:51:46.709Z",codex-root,Sensitive-output safety must be enforced both at payload construction and at the final output sink. Tests now assert the config command never routes masked credentials through console logging.
